{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-9a08870393e29fff","input":{"filename":"action_report.md","title":"Documentation QA Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Documentation QA – Prioritized Action Report\n\n**Context**: Dossier for the Documentation QA agent was loaded and the operational records were analyzed (top 3 records, risk/opportunity scores). This informs immediate work focus.\n\n## Findings & Prioritization\n\n| Rank | Record ID | Title | Status | Impact | Risk Score | Opportunity | Issue Type |\n|------|----------|-------|--------|--------|------------|------------|------------|\n| 1 | 16‑A | Documentation QA priority case | urgent | 47,072 | 7 (high) | 6.7 | **Factual bug / missing prerequisite** |\n| 2 | 16‑C | Documentation QA blocked follow‑up | blocked | 21,376 | 5 (medium) | 2.1 | **Ambiguity / dependency** |\n| 3 | 16‑B | Documentation QA routine queue item | in_review | 10,808 | 2 (low) | 1.1 | **Stale example** |\n\n## Recommended Actions\n\n1. **Address Record 16‑A (Urgent)**\n   - Conduct a focused audit of the high‑impact documentation sections identified in the record.\n   - Fix broken promises and add explicit prerequisites where missing.\n   - Tag each change as **factual‑bug** or **missing‑prerequisite** for traceability.\n2. **Resolve Blocker in Record 16‑C**\n   - Identify the cross‑functional dependency (e.g., product team sign‑off) that is causing the block.\n   - Open a coordination ticket and set a clear deadline.\n   - Until resolved, treat the item as **ambiguity** and monitor for escalation.\n3. **Refresh Record 16‑B (Routine)**\n   - Review the example commands; replace any stale CLI syntax with current versions.\n   - Mark updates as **stale‑example** fixes and merge into the routine queue.\n\n## Next Steps\n- Assign ownership: urgent audit to lead docs engineer, blocker coordination to the program manager, routine updates to the junior docs reviewer.\n- Schedule a 2‑day sprint to close Record 16‑A; follow‑up meeting after blocker resolution.\n- Log all changes in the documentation QA tracking board with the issue type tags.\n\n*Assumptions*: Impact numbers derive from internal scoring; no external data sources were consulted.\n*Evidence*: Dossier loaded, records analyzed (see tool output)."},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:12:09.826Z"}}
